The paper discusses a method for integrating formal quantitative safety analysis methods into the development process of safety-critical systems using UML models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of formal methods, which could place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of automated translation, which could suggest the use of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper mentions the hiding of the analysis model and formal methods from the user, which could suggest the use of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO).
